part.name: Space usage in bytes
part.footNote: Multiple address spaces may be mapped at the same (physical) memory address ranges. Physical memory allocated (i.e. used) for sections in the given space are called "Native used Rom" and "Native used Ram" whereas memory allocated by other spaces is called "Foreign used" memory.

table.row: *;The function has a separate tree since it has 2 or more callers.
R;This function is part of a recursive call chain. If both a leaf and the root of a tree are marked this way, all nodes in between are in a recursive chain.
[<stack>:<s>,<a>; ...];For each stack the stack usage by the function itself (<s>) and the stack usage by the function and all its callees (<a>).
